The Thethtil Fan collection~
Set amidst the cyclopean arches, gargantuan doors, and clever yet
oh-so-whimsical traps of the tomb, this room is filled with Thethtil
paraphanelia.  A large poster depicts Thethtil in concert, while various
ancient alatharya trading cards lie scattered on the ground.  Thethtil\@s
appearance in Ancient Tomb Maker\@s monthly is made prominent use of, with a
framed copy of the front cover on one wall.  

Possible uses:

The Tomb will have a few sentient statues made by Dilalyn at the end of the
three Trials.  

Thethtil, having predicted the Sundering, created this Tomb as a way to
exact revenge upon the gods.  

The Tomb houses many pre-Sundering artifacts.  It doesn\@t really make sense,
though, for them to have survived the Sundering intact if they are
non-sphere related...  So perhaps Thethtil designed them to be potent
manifestations of the spheres (so there would be at least one each of air,
earth, fire, void...  Perhaps water but probably not spirit) .  Also, as he
was smart enough to predict the Sundering he may have had some insight into
how it would manifest.  

Possibly re-use one of the alchemical affects that will not be re-used in
some form.  They will be less OP strictly by nature of being limited and
hard to get as opposed to brew some random shit into a potion.  

The result of the three Trials can have a cumulative outcome.  Make an
object that has specific qualities based on completion.  For example, a
weapon that is normal, then when one trial is completed gains some permanent
hitroll/damroll boost, then gains some other quality and finally can be
permanently typed to a particular damage.  

- Multiple endings for the trials, which determine the qualities imbued in
the resulting object.  

Need to entertain multiple people while one is here getting the result. 
Maybe use single-use portals to separate the \#active\# person from the rest
of the group for the final tests.  

