#2202
A Marble Chamber~
This chamber is carved out of the stone of solid marble, polished smooth,
and completely free of imperfections.  Shaped in the fashion of a
tetrahedron, the most prominent feature of this chamber are three statues,
build to cover the three corners of the room.  The statues are roughly
twelve feet in height, and they all look down on a spiral stairwell,
descending in a well in the center of the room.  While there is no source of
light in the room, a dim ambient glow fills the air, accentuating the
craftsmanship of the statues.  In the south wall, a rounded stone door,
framed by stout pillars, provides another exit from this chamber.  
