maker.  Enormous pillars jut upward on either side of the chamber, rising
into arches to create semicircular tops of gigantic niches.  In each niche,
carved out of blocks of marble, are the statues of epic proportion and
legendary quality.  The largest statue, though, lies to the north, depicted
as holding the weight of the celing on his shoulders.  Beneath him,
triumphal arches lead out of the long hall.  The only other exit lies
upward, where a gargantuan stairwell leads upward from its spot in the south
wall.  
