#2305
Beneath a Crystaline Dome~
A perfect hemisphere of crystal streches overhead, made of interlocking
facets of some clear and highly refractive gemstone.  An iridescent light
fills the top of the chamber, bathing the dome in a shimmering pattern of
multicolored light.  The floor of the chamber consists mainly of a sequence
of circular steps, which narrow as they rise.  At their top is a stand of
untarnished gold, which holds a shard of the same crystal as the dome above.
Between the boundary of the crystal dome and the marble walls of the room is
a frieze, set in bas relief around the circumference of the room, depicting
ancient alatharya in various activities.  There are four exits from this
circular room, one for each cardinal direction.  To the south, there lies a
triumphal arch, beyond which is visible another chamber.  The other three
exists are all marble doorways, each adorned only with a sigil, carved in
the top of their frames.  
~
